As for the comments about me working for AO because I make negative comments about EQ, that is just silly.  It is an accepted marketing norm that happy and content consumers are quiet consumers in terms of a public forum, and what you speak of about your Dodge truck is word of mouth praise among your own circle of family and close friends.  It is very rare to see public praise for a company or product unless A) The company has gone above and beyond the call of duty, and an overwhelming amount of consumers are happy and excited about the said product/company or B) The person giving praise is being paid to do it, either by the said company in terms of press releases, or by a 3rd party publication who uses reviews and opinions of said product(s) to attract readers.  Personally, I have yet to see any praise for Verant or EQ on these boards, but I do seem to see a good bit of negative comments about EQ and Verant, leading me to believe that consumers are not happy and content.  The reason people stay?  What other choice do we have?  A good number of people migrated to DAoC when it was released, only to discover that it wasn't as great as they thought it would be, so they have returned to EQ, which is what they know and love.  Its almost as if Verant has a monopoly of sorts on the fantasy MMORPG market, yet they see the end of this monopoly coming, so they are trying to squeeze every last cent out of it now while the massive amount of users are still willing to pay and not simply cancel and move to something else.  I give Verant credit on that, they have made a good business decision in those terms, but in my opinion, they should still be pushing hard to expand and retain more users instead of maximizing profits before they dump EQ to put all their support behind Star Wars Galaxies.<br>
<br>
And finally... you admit yourself of one of the major shortcomings of EQ in your reply (interface) yet you roll over and take it without even flinching, even going as far as to praise Verant and EQ.  That makes you look like a follower, and not a leader.  I for one have trouble putting stock in anyones comments that get charged more money for the same exact thing, and happily accept it without argument.<br>
<br>
Fannyar<br>
54 Cleric<br>
